definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  H(2)O + 2 NAD(+) + UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine -eq- 3 H(+) + 2 NADH + UDP-N-acetyl-2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucuronate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADP+ + 16-alpha-hydroxysteroid -eq- NADPH + H+ + 16-oxosteroid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD(P)+ + 17-alpha,20-alpha-dihydroxypregn-4-en-3-one -eq- NAD(P)H + H+ + 17-alpha-hydroxyprogesterone.

Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-pantolactone + NADP+ -eq- 2-dehydropantolactone + NADPH + H+. The reaction is A-specific (i.e. the pro-R hydrogen is transferred from the 4-position of reduced nicotinamide cofactor) with respect to NADP+.

Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD+ + 2-methyl-3-hydroxybutyryl-CoA -eq- NADH + H+ + 2-methylaceto-acetyl-CoA.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NAD+ + 7-alpha-hydroxycholesterol -eq- NADH + H+ + 7-alpha-hydroxycholest-4-en-3-one.
Catalysis of the reaction -  NADP+ + (5Z,13E)-(15S)-9-alpha,11-alpha,15-trihydroxyprosta-5,13-dienoate -eq- NADPH + H+ + (5Z,13E)-(15S)-9-alpha,15-dihydroxy-11-oxoprosta-5,13-dienoate.
